1 unit Black Beans
6 unit Flour Tortillas
1 unit Sweet Bell Pepper
113 g Baby Tomatoes
1 unit Yellow Onion
56 g Spring Mix
1 cup Monterey Jack Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
2 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
1 tbsp Enchilada Spice Blend
1 tbsp Rice Vinegar
2.33 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
¼ tsp Sugar*
2 unit Beyond Meat®

Before starting, preheat the oven to 450˚F.Wash and dry all produce. Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch pieces.Halve tomatoes.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, Beyond Meat® patties, onions and three-quarters of the peppers. Cook, breaking up patties into bite-sized pieces, until crispy, 5-6 min.\*\* Meanwhile, using a strainer, drain and rinse black beans.Add black beans to a large bowl, then, using the back of a fork, lightly mash until they just burst.

Add Enchilada Spice Blend to Beyond Meat® and veggies. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 30 sec.Remove the pan from heat. Add tomato sauce base, chipotle sauce and black beans.Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Arrange tortillas on a clean surface.Using a spoon, divide Beyond Meat® and bean mixture down the middle of each tortilla.Sprinkle half the cheese over top.Roll tortillas tightly over filling, then arrange them on a parchment-lined baking sheet, seam-side down.Brush taquitos with 1 tsp (2 tsp) oil, then sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Bake in the middle of the oven until golden-brown, 7-10 min.

Meanwhile, add vinegar, 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) sugar to the same bowl used to mash black beans. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.

Add tomatoes, spring mix and remaining peppers to the bowl with dressing. Toss to coat.Divide taquitos and salad between plates.